M=(1/2)*D+(1/2)*C;

draw(B--M);

draw(A--C);

label("$A$",A,NW);
label("$B$",B,NE);
label("$C$",C,SE);
label("$D$",D,SW);
label("$O$",(0.5,0.3));
label("$M$",M,S);

label("$45^\circ$", (0.2,0.1));
label("$45^\circ$", (0.8,0.1));
label("$45^\circ$", (0.6,0.4));

[/asy]

Now, let $x = CM = MD$.  Then $CD = 2x$, so $AD = 2x$.  Then $AC = AD \cdot \sqrt{2} = 2x \sqrt{2}$.

Since $\triangle OAC$ is a right triangle, $OA = AC - OC = 2x \sqrt{2} - x \sqrt{2} / 2 = \frac{3}{2} x \sqrt{2}$.

Therefore, the ratio of $OC$ to $OA$ is $\frac{x \sqrt{2} / 2}{\frac{3}{2} x \sqrt{2}} = \boxed{\frac{1}{3}}$.

